Grapefruit juice was already suspected to be responsible for increasing the effects of some medicines such as antibiotics, antiasthmatics, cardiovascular medicines, anxiolytic and neurological agents to toxic levels.
MEDIKAMENTE IN GEFAHR - The same agency of the medicine had warned doctors and patients in a report two years ago about the dangers of this mixture, and stressed that attention should be paid to what is being drunk in conjunction with medicines such as diazepan or metadone.
IT'S NOT SUPPLY - According to experts, orange juice and apple juice also contain substances that can inhibit the medicines.
The list of active substances that are blocked by the fruit juices is long.
Therefore, the appeal of Michele Carruba, Director of the University Statale di Milano: "Such results are usually forwarded immediately to the various international manufacturers, which are so free to change consumer information.
